inn1.comm: full length ball from over the wicket, Guptill leans out into a compact defensive
angled across at 122 kph, that didn't really bounce high off the track and Guptill steered it into the covers

manic start to the run-scoring for the day. Back of a length on the pads, Guptill nudged it softly towards Hafeez at mid-on and took off like a man possessed. He put in the dive and made his ground comfortably, but the throw missed in any case.
How adjusts late as some late movement away from off stump tries to square him up
fuller at 125 kph, How opens the face as he reaches out and steers it defensively towards point
another tight single in the same direction. Late movement again for Tanvir, coming in from well outside leg stump, How goes back to work it off the pads to mid-on
back of a length on off stump and coming in, How works it off the pads towards midwicket
nice lift from outside off, Razzaq lands is short of a length at 127 kph and How rides the bounce to defend off the back foot
and the fielder comes into play there, this one tails into the pads and How gets it fine off the pads. Doesn't make good enough contact with it for runs
another one sliding down the leg side, through to the keeper off the pads.

superb stuff on show. Razzaq drops it a touch fuller and How is ready with a crunchy straight drive that seems destined for four ... until Wahab runs across from mid on and dives full length to stop it and nearly produce a run out as the batsmen scramble a single
back of a length outside off to end the over, Guptill defends
slips down the leg side, seemed to clip How's pad on the way, but it is called a wide
better line, angling across the right hander who defends into the off side

whoa, How has thumped this, and how. He walks down the track with intent, converts a back of length delivery into a half-volley and drills it straight towards Gul at mid on, but it bursts through his effort and speeds away for four.
good response from Sohair, gets this one to swerve away from back of a length and How leaves

bham. Short ball from Sohail, not short enough for the pull, but not fast enough to hustle the batsman either. How goes for the pull shot, and despite being cramped for room makes good enough connection to nearly clear midwicket

leading edge, falls safe. Again Sohail gets that late away movement going, How closes the face early in his eagerness to ping the leg side boundary, and the edge flies between extra cover and point, short of Umar Akmal at point, who then misfields, as the ball spins past him.
and that's a very poor ball to end the over. Strays onto the pads with fine leg inside the circle and How does the needful - glances it away without a fuss for four more
back of a length outside off, How stays back in the crease and defends
similar ball, angling in from back of a length at 130 kph and How hangs back to defend again
fuller, that was an attempted legcutter on off stump, but How had it covered off the front foot
on a length again, pushed away to the off side
fractionally shorter on off stump and How is beside himself in glee as he eyes the leg side boundary with another quick swivel and pull, but this one is onto him too quickly for the shot
Razzaq delivers a fine maiden, another one back of a length outside off and How treats it with respect
Sohail's radar is not working. Well down the leg side, Guptill doesn't really attempt a shot as it trickles away off his pads towards fine leg, but the umpire declares leg byes
better line, angles in sharply from wide of the crease and Guptill punches to mid on with the full face

Guptill smokes the square drive in imperious style. Very full from Sohail, a foot wide of the stumps and Guptill gets half across and just frees his hands through point. That just bounded away off the willow.
comes in again, tightening the line and cutting off the room. Guptill plays straight to mid on
and again the width, Guptill can't quite place the cover drive, and finds the fielder
finishes with one that kicks up off a length and Guptill is a little bemused as he takes the bottom hand off and guides it behind square
full-pitched, How drives back past the bowler for a single as mid-on comes across
thick edge, but safely away through backward point for four. Guptill did not get across enough to have that under control and it flew very quickly past Umar Akmal at point
shot of the morning. Guptill siezes a short ball early, and gets into position well before it comes on to him and swats it elegantly over midwicket. Classy.
fuller, 129 kph on the pads, Guptill works it towards wide mid on for a single
How goes back to a back of length delivery and punches into the covers
straighter this time, but How can't place the on drive past mid on
monster short ball, well down the leg side and it is another wide. Pakistan are struggling a bit here.
more like it, whangs this short of a length outside off and gets it to lift nicely into Guptill who defends off the back foot
Guptill sets himself up for another swivel pull, but Riaz is onto him at 139 kph and Guptill can't time the shot.
on a length, on the pads, and How nudges to the right of mid on for another single

nicely taken by Younis at short midwicket. Guptill is dismissed again the run of play, in extremely soft fashion. He shakes his head in disappointment, he's missed out on a pitch full of runs. Riaz wisely lands another one short of driving length and Guptill stays back in the crease and looks to work it to the leg side. He can't keep it completely down, though, and Younis was on the move even as he played the shot, tumbling to his left to take a neat catch.
similar ball, short and on the stumps, Taylor shuffles across and defends to the leg side. This time, he keeps it down.
Taylor is away with a whiplash through point. The slightest hint of room outside off as Riaz angles across and Taylor sets himself up for the slash-cut with his trigger movement and connects crisply.
back of a length from Razzaq, he's been very disciplined today. How goes back and defends to the off side
huge appeal for lbw turned down.. 130 kph and nipping in off the seam from middle stump as How misses the flick. That was surely heading down the leg side
back on off stump line, How plays it back down the track compactly
How opens the face and looks to dab past point, but can't beat the fielder

and that walk down the track again, he doesn't do it consistently like Hayden or Gambhir would - he uses it more as a rare surprise weapon. It is however, not there for the swipe or the drive of the flick. He ends up working it into the covers

How tragic! How has picked Umar Akmal at the midwicket fence with pin-point accuracy. Almost scientific precision. Short ball, it was there for the pull and How connected cleanly. That seemed headed for a flat six, but Umar was waiting with glee.
wide of off stump and Taylor lets it go
goes across and defends one from middle and leg towards midwicket

three wickets in three overs, New Zealand are disintegrating. And like the previous two, this is another wicket gifted away. Riaz explores a fuller length, lands it enticingly for the drive outside off and Taylor takes him on, attempting the big booming cover drive. He was so eager to get four, he did not get across enough and just threw his hands at it. The result was a thick outside edge that flew to Younis at slip.
back of a length outside off, KW goes back and defends
this one angles across him and he lets it go
a quiet finish to the over as KW again deals with a delivery outside off defensively
Styris opens the face and defends from the crease to the off side
superb delivery, legcutter nipping away, perilously close to the outside edge as Styris hangs his bat out there in hope.
onto the pads, Styris can't make connection with the flick
on that perfect length outside off again, Styris gets behind the line and defends
on the stumps this time, Styris looks to get across and work to the leg side, but can't get it away
another maiden from Razzaq, who has been the best bowler of the day so far. Keeps it short of a length outside off again, nothing Styris can do with it, without taking a risk. He doesn't.
angled across from over the wicket, lively bounce from outside off and KW steers it to cover
the dot-ball sequence is ended with a manic single. KW dabs into the covers and Umar Akmal has a shy, but KW is really quick and makes it in time. The throw missed in any case.
Styris stays back and defends to the leg side
back of a length again, angling across Styris who defends to the off side
angling across again, at 137 kph, Styris is watchful with the check drive from the crease towards mid off

cut away for four, in the air, but safely over point. There was room on offer and it was short enough for the shot, and Styris decided to go through with it despite the gravity of the situation. Gets under it on purpose and sends it over the cordon.
KW perches on the back foot and defends towards mid off
drifts into middle and leg, KW works it neatly off the pads, but straight to midwicket
slow bouncer, 123 kph and KW gets under it as it balloons across the turf
short and drifting into the body, KW nudges square for NZ's 50th run
Styris hangs back to a short of length delivery and defends to the covers
back of a length outside off to end the over and Styris pushes it towards cover point
back of a length and angling across KW who punches off the back foot into the covers
and again, KW goes back in the crease and defends to the leg side
this one is on the pads and is eased away through square leg for one
on Styris' middle and leg, he works it cautiously to the leg side
Sohail gets one to nip away disconcertingly at 123 kph and Styris has to adjust quickly to defend to the off side
Styris gets one on the pads and clips it square for a single to retain strike
Razzaq darts one in from outside off and Styris plays from the crease back down the track
and this one holds its line outside off, while Styris plays outside the line and gets a thick inside edge through square leg
KW forces one from off and middle to the leg side for another single
Styris hangs in the crease and defends to the off side
rare driving length delivery from Styris and he times the extra cover drive well, but can't find the gap
another crisply timed shot, this time square, but straight to the fielder
guided into the covers off the back foot, they just can't find the gaps now.
KW powers the on-drive past mid-on with a special bit of timing. Over-pitched on the pads, he adjusted well to ensure he got it to the right of mid-on and it just kept going. Three runs taken.
Styris has a lazy waft outside off as Sohail gets one to angle across him. Close to the edge
rides the bounce this time, opens the face and steers towards point
and this time he times the square cut perfectly. Inch-perfect lack of placement. Straight to point

Styris releases the load of pressure on his shoulders with a sprightly straight drive past the off-colour Sohail. In the bowler's defence, this wasn't his worst ball of the day - just short of driving length on middle and leg. But Styris was good enough to walk into position and punch it with the full face down the ground
and whangs the first ball too short and wide down the leg side
iffy start this from Gul, 137 kph well down the leg side and another wide
finally hits an acceptable line, a touch outside off and back of a length. KW comes forward and punches into covers
angled into the body, KW stays in the crease and works it square for one
Styris hangs back and steers a back of length ball towards point
on the pads, Styris can't get bat on it, but they steal a leg bye to the leg side
on the pads again, KW gets inside the line and clips behind square for one
yorker, 141 kph outside off and nearly caught Styris napping. He jams the bat down on it and keeps it out to the off side
turns in from outside off at 85 kph, he rocks back and forces it against the spin into the covers
fuller on middle, Styris works it down to long on for a single

Styris is run out. As if shot selection issues were not enough, New Zealand now endure a communication breakdown. This was turning into KW from wide of off stump, he shaped for the cut and played it carefully towards cover-point. Styris wanted one and charged out. KW kept asking him to wait, but clearly his plea went unheard. Styris turned back belatedly, but was caught well short before the throw from Gul came back to the bowler and the stumps were broken.
topspinner on off, KW defends off the front foot

I thought that was a replay. Franklin is almost run out following another Styris-esque piece of bizarre running. Full on off, KW leans out and drives into the covers. There is a yes and a no, and there is blind stop-start running from Franklin, who turns back too late. Afridi's throw was poor, else he would have been gone.
back of a length outside off, Franklin goes back and defends to the off side
short and slightly wide, looks for the cut but can't get the gap
holds the length ball and angles it across Franklin who defends to the off side
bouncer at 135 kph and a good one. Franklin drops his wrists and lets it go
over-pitched on the pads, there for the flick, but Franklin finds wide mid on

all timing from Franklin. The flick shot was barely a feather touch. It simply purred away off the sweetest spot. Length ball on the pads, he got into position early and just coaxed it away, in the air, but well wide of mid-on.
worked with the spins towards Misbah at mid on
looks to work him off the pads with the spin, but can't get it away
Hafeez hangs back to defend as it turns in from outside off
stays back and looks to work it to the leg side once again, but can't find the gap
KW eventually gets the single, punching a full ball on the stumps back down the track
this one slides down the leg and is called wide
fired into Franklin's pads as he misses the flick and it runs away to the off side, towards short third man
fastish legspinner outside off, KW looks to cut and finds point
this one skids through at 92 kph and KW stays back and tries to force it away, but it is onto him too fast
this one tails in sharply and hits KW's pads, but it was sliding down.
marginally short and KW latches on early with a heaved pull shot over the infield. It is away for a rare four
quicker one, 100 kph and KW is hurried into the shot. Dribbles away to midwicket
and raps him on the pads with the last delivery, as KW looks to flick and plays all over it. Phew, what a fast over!
Franklin drives through mid-on for a single
slowed through the air, turning into KW who is forced to defend after thinking of the steer

KW combusts now. He jumps out of the crease, but is fooled in the flight and doesn't get to the pitch. He looks to go through with the loft down the ground, but can't make a clean connection. Who else by Younis Khan at long on to snaffle the mis-hit. New Zealand are ticking off all the bad shots in the book today.
tossed up from round the wicket, pushed away with the spin to the off side
similar ball, dealt with defensiively.
stays back and steers a delivery as it turns away, through point for one
fuller outside off driven to extra cover
bang on target, defended down the track
drops it a touch short and on leg stump, tickled away behind square leg
quicker, 96 kph, he can only push it back to Afridi
another fastish delivery around off stump, he gets forward and pushes out towards extra cover
can't get him away, no room at all, patted back down the pitch
the one that goes straight on, he was lured into the drive, and got an airy outside edge past short third man, could ave gone to him straight as well
pushed back down the track off the front foot
leans forward and pushes out to cover
gets a shortish one this time, and works it square off the back foot, still no run though
flighted a touch now, but on the stumps, can't do much with those
misses out on some runs here, it was turning down leg, but he cannot beat a diving square leg
tips it into the covers for a single
got him to rush down the track, it was bowled flatter and quicker, McCullum adjusted hurriedly to defend it towards covers
some hesitation here as he pushes one towards mid off and they flirt with the idea of a single
more hesitation now, James wants the run, Brendon doesn't, Misbah fields at mid off
flicked away towards mid wicket
hits it out to sweeper cover for a single
cut away to sweeper cover
goes on the back foot, but Hafeez is bang on middle, and he can only push it down the track
strays down the leg side as he looks to cramp him for room
gets some width outside off now, and cuts it away to sweeper cover
worked away wide of extra cover
tries the reverse sweep now, dangerous ploy with a short third man in place, it scoots away to that man for a single
goes round the wicket, flighted on off stump, driven down the pitch
Afridi continues the squeeze, another one played out to extra cover off the back foot
and another one, cannot beat that man at extra cover
a touch short from Shahid, he rocks back in a flash and cuts, but there is sweeper cover in place, and only a single results
hit down to long on, they need to keep taking these singles
goes for the cut, it was bowled quicker and got more bounce, he got a top edge that could have gone anywhere but went over short third man in the end, lucky
slapped away to sweeper cover
gets forward and eases this one bowled from round the stumps through extra cover for a single
hares down the track, Hafeez saw him coming and bowled it shorter, Brendown found the only man in the ring on the leg side at midwicket
brings up the 100 finally with a nudge past square leg
gets a thickish outside edge to short third man
pings extra cover with the back foot punch, cute shot for no runs
misses out this time, went back looking to work it away square but was hit on the pads, going down leg easily though
Baz gets forward, taps it into the covers, and off they go for the run

do we have a boundary, er, we don't! Shahid gave James some flight outside off, and he capitalised driving cleanly through extra cover, the man running across from long off put in the dive to save some runs
much flatter and quicker, pushed back to Shahid
driven to extra cover
swept away to Younis Khan at fine leg
gets a single down to long on
Baz rushes down  the track and works this shortish one away through square leg
calmly eased away to sweeper cover off the back foot
it was a touch short and Baz shaped up for the pull, but it got on to him much quicker and he adjust to hit it along the ground to deep midwicket
James continues to play those calm punches to sweeper cover
this time we have a boundary, Baz was quick to get to the pitch of this flighted one and loft it cleanly to the right of long off
now the reverse sweep, but won't get to the boundary this time, good over for New Zealand this
hit away down to long on for a single
that man at sweeper cover is in business again, as Baz cuts a short and wide ball to him
pushed out to point off the front foot
on leg stump, easy pickings, beats a diving midwicket with the push

down on one knee goes Baz and launches him wide of long on, who brings off an absolute beauty, it had bounced just short of the ropes and was about to land on the other side but he stretched out his right hand and pulled it back
pushed out to covers off the back foot
Baz gets some pace, and capitalises, there was some width too outside off, and he cut it past a helpless sweeper cover for a boundary
Wahab overcompensates down the leg side this time, and Baz works it away wide of fine leg, and then comes back for the second, putting in the big dive and all, excellent running
the slower one around off stump, he picks it up, and steers it down to third man
James brings up the 50 of the partnership with a back foot punch down the ground, and it has come in good time too
another slower one from Wahab, this time Baz cannot get it away, leans forward and pushes it out to point
short and wide, but at 106 kph, Baz cannot get it away even as he looks to slap it away through extra cover, ends up bottom edging it in to the ground
starts off with a length ball on middle stump which is driven straight to mid off by James
bowls his stock back of a length delivery, but a touch wide outside off and he cuts it away to sweeper cover
144 kph length delivery, but down the leg side, and off the pads and into the fine boundary, given as wides, hmm, there was a deflection there
shot! short but again down the leg side, Baz launches in to a violent short-arm pull and sends it crashing into the fine leg boundary
much better from Gul, back of a length around off, played out to point off the back foot, there were some premature thoughts of a single in Baz's mind but he rightly abandoned them
still more short of a good length from Umar, Baz cannot get it away, got in to an awkward position as he tried to ride some extra bounce that Umar got
this is a wayward return from Umar, strays down the leg side again
Baz latches onto another short ball down the leg side, but this time the one-legged pull shot goes straight to fine leg
143 kph delivery on leg, he makes some room outside his leg stump but misses out on the shot, playing inside the line

got 'em! Riaz with the breakthrough, it was a length delivery angled across Baz, who pushed at it inside the line with an angled bat, and Kamran happily gobbled the outside edge, Baz was looking good here, but has got out to a soft dismissal, well at least he has continues the trend
gets a short ball, ducks right into it, and is hit on the body, ouch!
has a lazy waft at one going across him, but he does not get the edge that Baz managed to, luckily
steered away to third man for a run
dropped it was cut away in the air to the left of point, who dived full length and got a hand to it, but could not latch onto it, very tough chance it was anyways
full outside off stump, he goes for the drive, but hits it straight to backward point
length ball on the stumps, defended off the back foot
Umar with that short of a good length delivery around off stump, he stands tall and defends it off the back foot, elegant but unproductive
gets far across the stumps, and works this length ball away to deep midwicket
good stuff from Gul this over, James stands in the crease and pushes out a back of a length ball out to extra cover
gives it a thump off the back foot, but Shahid puts in the dive at extra cover and saves some runs
140 kph short of a good length delivery around off stump, he rides the bounce, and brings it down towards point
has one more lazy waft at one that was angled across him, but no edge fortunately for Nathan
gives him the bouncer now on leg stump, Nathan lets it fly over him
Nathan gets bat on ball this time, punches this one away to sweeper cover off the back foot
looks to drive it past the bowler, but does not get any timing on it, and Wahab fields in his follow through
bowls a length ball on the pads, he whips it down to fine leg to retain the strike
gets some room outside off and drives this one past point, third man runs in and does the fielding
Gul with the yorker, raps him on the pads and goes up in appeal, but that struck him outside leg stump
lovely free-flowing drive from James, got one in the slot outside off stump and eased it away to the left of sweeper cover
143 kph bouncer from Gul, what a reply after that boundary, James did well to get out of the line as it got big on him, and thudded into Kamran's gloves
bowls him the fast full toss, Franklin hits it straight back to the bowler, who dons a menacing expression and throws it back to the keeper

gets an outside edge as Franklin hangs his bat to a short of a good length ball, but no slips at this stage of the innings, and that will runaway in to the fine third man boundary, frustration for Umar after a superb over
played back to the bowler off the back foot
goes down on a knee and thumps it along the ground, but straight to sweeper cover
strays down the leg side with a length delivery
good delivery, tucking him up for room around middle stump, he adjusts to push it out to short midwicket
the bouncer arrives from Riaz, James goes underneath it, Kamran collects
misses out on the attempted flick to a length ball on the pads, but even as it rolls away on the leg side, they sneak a single
played out to short midwicket off the back foot, miserly over from Wahab
the wrong 'un, pushed back down the track
slapped away to extra cover off the back foot
skiddy, slipper stuff from Afridi, he almost gets his man as he drives in the air, but fortunately for him, in the gap through covers
driven to sweeper cove for a single
sweeps this fullish one behind square leg for another run
nudged away to short fine leg and they rush through for a single
short and too far wide outside off stump from back of a length
another short and wide delivery, slapped away to sweeper cover off the back foot
surprised by the slower one, pushes it out to extra cover
they steal a run ever so sneakily, James missed out on the attempted whip across the line, and Nathan willed him into crossing over
steered down to third man
bangs it in short, and he goes for the pull, getting it just over midwicket, Wahab runs across and prevents the boundary
this one almost got through the gap between bat and pad, he got an inside edge that saved him as the ball rolled away to Umar at square leg
watchfully forward in defence is Nathan
cuts without power and cannot get it past short third man
leans forward and square droves but this time finds backward point
gets the single this time, pushes this one on off stump towards midwicket
gets a top edge as he swivels to pull a short one, but it falls well short of Younis Khan on the backward square leg boundary who does well to stop it inside the ropes
as close to a perfect forward defensive as you will ever get, lovely to watch, but the scoreboard remain the same
waits for this slower one to arrive and cuts it in the gap between cover and point for a boundary, good start to the Powerplay
another slower one from Tanvir, this time he cannot get it past extra cover
this time he bowls the yorker outside off stump, and James manages to squeeze it past short third man for a boundary, got his bat down just in time
James brings up his 50 with a neat whip off his legs that goes into the fine leg boundary, well played, he has been in good form recently
driven down the ground on the leg side off the front foot
one more slower one from Sohail, Nathan can only push it back down the track
143 kph yorker from Gul, James somehow manages to dig it out towards extra cover
makes some room outside leg and gives it a good swipe, but the ball was around a foot away from his bat
goes for the yorker again but this time it ends up as a full toss, he pushes it hastily down the ground for a single
147 kph from Gul, but a touch overpitched around off stump, and James drives it with excellent timing through extra cover for a boundary

oh dear, oh dear, Gul has made a total mess of a simple run out, James was miles out of his ground attempting a non-existent single to point, the thrown came Gul's away nicely over the stumps, but he failed to collect it cleanly, and James can't believe his luck
fast and furious length ball on the stumps, hit out towards extra cover
Nathan looks to go downtown over midwicket, but misses the length ball going across him completely, and Kamran collects
plants the front foot down the track and goes for another heave-ho, but Wahab bowled it wider this time, and he misses out again
three in three! he walked outside off stump, and gave it everything possible, the only thing he did not manage was to get bat on ball
bows it wide outside off stump this time, Nathan gave it the swing anyway
and our man connects this time, past a diving Younis Khan at midwicket and into the boundary
Riaz oversteps in his eagerness to angle it past the batsman, Nathan did what he has been doing all over, and the result was the same, but he gets a free hit
this time he walks some two feet outside off stump and flicks this length ball past square leg
James' luck continues to favour him, he gets an inside edge that barely misses the stumps, Nathan goes through for the single, puts in the dive even as Kamran misses with the throw
Franklin goes aerial over the leg side, but the top edge falls well short of wide long on
lovely fielding at cover, dives to his left to save a certain boundary, it was cut fiercely by Nathan
goes for the sweep and misses out, is hit on the pads
Franklin departs, goes for the big swing over square leg, and hits it straight down the throat of Riaz at deep backward square leg, but he's got NZ past 200, how much more can they get?
gets a thick outside edge that rolls away to short third man
goes back and gives it a good old thwack, and the thick edge loops away in the gap between cover and backward point, and only some fine fielding prevents a boundary
Nathan has absolutely creamed this full delivery through cover, sweeper cover was a spectator, that pinged the boundary in a flash
yorker outside the off stump, he goes for another swing, and another miss results
how did he do this? it was full and heading for the stumps, but Nathan scooped it perfectly over short fine leg, took it almost off the stumps as he went down on one knee
rushes down the track blindly, and swings across the line, the ball rolls away off the body into the off side
the bouncer from Wahab but high above the batsman, and is called a wide
short and wide outside off again, too wide to be called one again
goes for a drive to a length delivery, and gets it off the inner half of the bat back to Wahab
Wahab's radar has oscillated wildly this over, this time he goes wide down the leg side
good delivery to finish a very productive Powerplay for the batting side, full and on the stumps, squeezed down the ground for a single
goes down to sweep this full ball in front of square leg
much slower and more flight from Shahid, swung down the ground, long on does the tidying up
goes for a half-hearted half-sweep, and gets a top edge in to the leg side
goes for the reverse sweep now, and it loops up in the air for Kamran to pouch it, and they all go up in appeal, umpire reckons there was no bat there
looks to hit this one down the ground but the ball rolls away to Shahid
reverse swept straight to backward point
101 kph slower one from round the stumps, he manages to limply push it out to point
straightens from a length on middle and off, he guides it to point, and they go through for the quick single
squeezes the yorker down the ground to long off, but the man there is quick on the ball, and a run is all that he allows
96 kph slower ball, he waits and waits for it to arrive, and cuts it over cover, but sweeper cover is there on the boundary
full delivery around off stump, smashed along the ground to long off
Dan walks across the stumps, Sohail targets them with a full delivery, but Vettori gets bat to it in time, and scoops it over short fine leg who leaps in vain
another cute scoop shot, this one goes barely to the left of Kamran but very high over him, it was a bit of a top edge but Nathan will take the boundary
makes a lot of room outside leg, but Gul follows him with a 140 kph back of a length ball, and Nathan could not connect with the wild flail
and another one, this time it bounces extra too, that is because Gul put in extra effort, and also managed to overstep
can't do anything with the free hit, it was full and outside off stump, he had backed too far away outside leg
Nathan with his almighty swing on one knee, but cannot connect with the length delivery again
this time he does connect, and very cleanly too, lifting a fuller delivery up and over extra cover, and into the boundary
off a thickish edge and down to third man for a single
goes very wide of the crease, and delivers a wide ball down the leg side
slower one outside off stump this time, and Nathan gives it the heave, for effect
alright, this one is not for effect, it was short, sitting up around off, and he made some room to lift it over extra cover for a six to move to 49

one more slower delivery, he looked to go for the scoop over short fine leg but the ball rolled away along the ground to that man, 50 up for Nathan, it has been agricultural at times, but mighty effective
flicked away to fine leg off the pads

gets the toe end of the bat as he shapes up for another one over short fine leg, the ball rolls away towards Tanvir, who ponders for a while, and that is enough time for them to go through for a wild run
hit away through midwicket for a single, Dan it will be on strike for the final over
backs away down the leg side, and Wahab bowls it wide outside off stump, Dan couldn't do anything on that occasion
goes way outside off stump now, Riaz follows him there, and he squeezes out the full delivery down to third man
drops it a touch short now, and he goes for the pull but straight to the man on the deep square leg boundary
full and tight from Wahab on the stumps, pushed out through extra cover for a single

goes for the pick up shot over fine leg from outside off stump, it rolls away fine off the pads, and they take two through some furious running, Nathan putting in the dive in the end even as the thrown comes in from Razzaq
end of a fine last over from Wahab as Nathan squeezes out a full delivery towards extra cover, but New Zealand will be happy after having slipped to 79 for 5

inn2.comm: a  bit of away shape first up from outside off stump, Hafeez gets a thick edge down to third man as he pushes at it from the crease

almost run out! it was pushed towards midwicket who hared in and fired in the throw at the non-striker's where the batsman had backed up too far and had to put in a desperate dive, but the throw missed in the end
looks to leave this one in the channel outside off stump, but is slow to weave his bat out of the line, and gets an edge that rolls away to third man
no problems in letting this one go, Southee helps matters by bowling it wide outside off
goo delivery, just about short of a length, and making him reach for it around off stump, he pushes it back airily down the track
digs it in to the batsman from short of a good length, who hops in the air and takes it on the body
one more almost leave, the resultant edge goes towards second slip but falls well short
not short enough, but he whips it away off the hips on one knee in front of square leg for the first boundary of the innings
bowls it a touch fuller around off stump, he leans forward to push it towards mid off
digs it in short, and Shehzad pounces on it in a flash, pulling it high and clean over mid on for another boundary
gets on top of the bounce off this back of a length ball, pushes it out to cover, and shouts out a loud 'NO'
Dan concedes a single at mid on, it was flicked wristily to his right, and he did not get down in time to stop it cleanly
takes a step forward to this shortish ball outside off, and lets it go
steady back of a length stuff from Tim outside off stump, gets a touch big on Hafeez who brings it down off the back foot
stands tall and meatily punches this back of a length ball outside off in to the gap at extra cover, boundary all the way
Southee bowls it fuller, and Shehzad pushes it back to him off the front foot
bangs in another shortish delivery, this time Shehzad is quick to get on the back foot, and swivels to pull it to the deep square leg boundary
more runs, he got across to a length ball around middle and leg, and whipped it elegantly down to the left of fine leg
Hafeez is much more cautious, lets this length ball come on to him and reaches out at the last instant to push it towards cover
New Zealand persist with the back of a length stuff, Shehzad again punches it in to the gap between cover and extra cover, but this time without much timing, and gets only the single
stretches forward and drives this length ball into the covers
lifter from Bennett outside off stump, Hafeez leaves it well alone, good judgment
more back of a length stuff, this time straight in to the body, he goes on the back foot and defends it back to the bowler
looks to whip this shortish delivery through midwicket, but gets it off the bottom half of the blade and the ball rolls away in to the leg side
stands tall and punches hard but straight in to the covers
this length is not troubling Pakistan at all, another short of a good length ball played out towards covers
a whisker fuller than the previous one, but wide enough outside off stump for the batsman to shoulder arms with a flourish
much fuller this time, flicked neatly off the pads too, but Styris at midwicket dives and saves some runs for his side
full delivery again, he gets forward and drives confidently to mid off
he is hitting them so crisply, but finding the fielders at the moment, another drive goes to widish mid off
goes too straight on the stumps and is picked away for a single through midwicket
on leg stump, worked away for single to midwicket
pushed in to the covers and off they go
worked away off the back foot to square leg
another one on the pads turned to square leg
this time he gets it in the gap past midwicket
gets away with a full toss, Shehzad hit it straight to the man at short midwicket
short and gets the treatment, pulled high in the air over midwicket, rolls away over the ropes to beat the man running in from deep square leg
Guptill with an acrobatic save at cover, took a few steps to his right and put in the dive at full stretch, it was thumped off the front foot
played out in to the off side
another short delivery, Shehzad rolls his wrists over the ball to pull it along the ground through midwicket
slightly back of a length around off stump, he is quick to get on to the back foot and punch it, but straight to extra cover
gets across to whip this angled length delivery but finds the man at midwicket
pushed away down to mid off for a single
99 kph flat delivery around off stump, he rocks back to cut it towards covers
bowls it way down the leg side, and he helps it on its way to the deep square leg boundary
pushed out to the covers
Nathan strays in line again, down the leg side again, and he sweeps it again backward of square for another boundary
makes room outside leg and punches it towards cover off the back foot
gets an inside edge on to pad as he shaped to clip this full ball through midwicket
punched away to cover off the back foot

Rosco has taken a blinder, it was forced away off the back foot, the outside edge flew fast and over Taylor at first slip, who leaped in the air with one hand outstretched, and brought down the ball with him
clipped away off the toes to the right of mid on for a single
very full delivery, almost yorker length, dug out back to the bowler
goes on the back foot and defends this short of a good length ball down the track
shortish around off stump, he backs away and cuts it, but to the man at point
goes for the cut again, this one was much quicker from Dan, and he got it past short third man for a boundary
slows it down a touch, and Kamran punches it to point off the back foot
shortish delivery around leg stump, pushed away wide of midwicket for a single
another boundary, brings up Pakistan's 50, it was there for the cut, and he got it in the gap past backward point, Dan has been on the shorter side this over
floats it up this time, and he turns it fine on the leg side where there is a man inside the ring

full delivery driven past the bowler, it is not timed well enough to go all the way, and they decide to go for the third even as the ball is pulled back near the ropes, and Kamran had to put in the dive to reach home on the end
short of a good length and outside the off stump, left well alone
full and on the pads, he cannot get it past midwicket with the clip
gets across and turns this one square on the leg side off the pads

dropped How pulled off another blinder, well almost, it was creamed off the front foot, and How dived in the air almost parallel to the ground at backward point, even got a hand to the ball, but put it down in the end
straightens ever so slightly from back of a length outside off stump, he is beaten as he goes for the attempted drive through extra cover
Dan starts off with one on the stumps this time, and he pushes it back to the bowler
bowling it slower this over, flighted outside off stump, and it is pushed out to cover
cannot get the full toss away, hits it straight to a diving short extra cover
leans forward and pushes in to the off side
nudged fine down the leg side, off the pads

down the track charges Shehzad, gets to the pitch of this tossed up delivery, and lofts it high over mid off, and the timing on that one is so good that it goes all the way, guess who fielded that one, one Shane Bond
driven towards the covers off the front foot
bounces it high over the batsman, not called a wide, he gets away with it
back of a length in to the body, he calmly plays it out in to the leg side off the back foot
pushed forward and runs this length ball down to third man with an open bat face
gets the front foot across to flick this one on the pads down to fine leg
out of nowhere, this one moves away from a length around off stump, Kamran had shaped up for the big drive, and was beaten totally
trundles in and bowls a gentle length ball on the stumps, and it is payed out towards short midwicket
this time he walks across the stumps, and works a similar delivery behind square leg
stands tall, and punches this one one front of square leg for another run

Styris gets the breakthrough, it was the seemingly gentle and harmless length delivery, Shehzad got lulled into a false sense of calmness and ended up flicking it straight to short midwicket, Kamran looks shocked, Shehzad was batting so well
gets a fuller ball around off stump, and defends it off the front foot
whips this one on middle and leg to short midwicket
Southee continues with his back-of-lengthers, this one is pushed out towards mid off
pitches it a touch fuller, and that much is enough for Kamran, who gets to the pitch and pings the gap at extra cover
reverts to short of a good length, and is worked away to short midwicket off the back foot
gets one in his area for the cut, but there are so many fielders lurking in that area that it will be a miracle if he can get it through them
the bouncer arrives from Southee, Kamaran goes down on one knee, and lets it fly over him
played out to point off the back foot
threaded into the gap through short midwicket and square leg
fuller delivery, driven along the ground to long on
shortish but does not get up much, he had shaped up for the pull but adjusted well to play it out to short midwicket in the end
gets a fuller one, and strides out to drive it down to long on
lovely late cut from Kamran, he waited for the ball to come on, and got it to the right of short third man, who ran and dived in to save some runs
fuller on the pads, flicked away through midwicket
shortish on the stumps, whipped away off the back foot in front of square leg
gets forward and drives to sweeper cover for a single
some turn for Dan, he rocks back and cuts it to sweeper cover
driven towards mid on off the front foot
right forward in defence to a ball on the middle stump
Dan prevents the single, it was punched away down the track, and he dived to his right to field the ball
nurdled fine on the leg side close to the stumps, Brendon fields
fired in on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
gentle stuff all around, length ball on the stumps, nudged away backward of square

well, well, Kamran has somehow managed to pick out Rosco at short midwicket, it was fuller on the stumps and he looked to go for the sweep, but hit it in the air to Taylor, who cannot believe his good fortune as he takes the dolly
played out to short midwicket
gets across and nurdles this one fine down the leg side, and is off the mark
goes for an ambitious pull shot, but it rolls away off the bottom half of the bat towards mid on
worked away backward of square leg off the back foot
sliding down the leg side straight on with the arm, he is hit on the pads as he looks to play it towards midwicket
worked away on the leg side for another single
another one, well almost, flicked dangerously in the air just past the man at short midwicket
goes back to one that was not short enough, and plays it out towards point
reaches out to defend this length ball back to Scott
punched away off the back foot towards mid off
waits for this one to come on and whips it away through square leg
another one nurdled away behind square for a run
reaches out and gets it past the non-striker to long on for a single
flicked airily in front of square leg, Scott is causing a few problems here
short ball, Misbah looks to pull, but fails to beat square leg
gets a single this time, fuller ball on leg stump, driven down to long on
Younis works Vettori deftly off the pads through square leg for a single
Misbah goes back in the crease and nudges Vettori off the pads through square for one
the softest of soft hands. Tapped daintily off the pads to the on side of the pitch and the veterans steal another single
Misbah tries to loot another single to the leg side, but can't get it far enough for McCullum to not be able to retrieve it on time
on middle and leg, full length, Younis works it back to the bowler
straighter from Styris, Younis works it past that man lurking at short midwicket, but this time the ball goes to his right for a single
back of a length outside off, Misbah reaches forward and defends
onto the pads, Misbah eases it off the pads behind square for one more
Younis tries to drive through mid off for a single, but it is straight enough for Styris to intercept
over-pitched on the pads and Younis resists the temptation to chip it to short midwicket. Plays it along the ground for a single
back of a length and turning away from Younis who steers with the spin through cover point for one
tossed up on Misbah's pads and he plays it softly to mid on
tight line, again on the stumps and Misbah plays it back to the bowler
this time Misbah gets his front foot across to chip a full delivery, at 91 kph,  through mid on for a single
Younis presses forward and drives with the spin through mid off for another single
nice loopy delivery on leg stump, not giving Misbah any pace to work with, and he can't get the soft flick away this time
short of a length from Styris, outside off, Younis stands tall and tries to force it past the on side, but can't get it past the man in the hotseat - short midwicket
whoa, tight run single that. Younis punches a full toss straight to mid off and takes off for a single., and barely makes it
this pitch is slowing up. Short ball, Misbah spotted it and set himself up for the pull, but it just died on him and he could not get bat on it
length ball on the pads, quietly nudged round the corner for a single
nice bit of timing on that extra-cover drive to a full length ball outside off, but Vettori, running across from mid off, does well to keep it down to one
Misbah shuffles across early and plays the flick from the off and middle line for a single through square leg
angles across at a friendly pace, Misbah stays back and guides into the covers for one

my, my, Younis is really testing the limits with these dangerous singles. Walks into an off drive, pinpoint straight to Williamson at mid off, who tries to throw the stumps down as Younis dives in. He misses, and Younis might have made it by inches.
and some release. Misbah looks to go inside out, over the covers but the timing is not a 100%. He manages to get it away for three.
Younis looks for a single into the covers, but can't find the gap this time
strays too far down the leg side and Younis gets the single with a glance just backward of square leg
full on the stumps, Misbah drives back and Franklin fields in his follow through
back of a length outside off, Younis stays back and punches through mid on for a single
slower ball, offcutter at 106 kph, but Misbah spotted it, camped well back in the crease, waited an eternity for it to come on and then worked it behind square for a couple
whoa, Misbah backs away to the leg side as Styris gets into delivery stride, comes back into position as he releases and then drives it back to the bowler
and again, Misbah is dancing around in the crease and Styris sticks to his guns - back of a length on the stumps. Quietly played through mid on for one
Younis waits in the crease, turns this one off the pads as it comes in with the angle
oriental wrists to the fore as Misbah gets half across and flicks from a foot outside off stump through midwicket.
Misbah waits for the ball to angle across and then opens the face to dab him safely to third man for one
Younis drops Franklin to the left of the pitch and they pinch another single
back of a length outside off and a touch of extra bounce, Misbah opens the face and steers square for one more
full ball, angles in at 124 kph, Younis gets forward and drives through the covers for another single to the deep
short of a length outside off, Misbah again looks to run it off the face, but plays this too square to elude point
some effort from Franklin, bangs it in at 136 kph and forces Misbah back. He rides the bounce and drops it to the off side, but can't get the run
nifty stuff from Younis, stays in the crease, waits for it to turn into him, tempts Brendon's gloves before dabbing it away at the last moment through third man
straighter, turns in from off, and Younis works it with the spin for a single through midwicket
Misbah picks a single now through midwicket
whoa, Nathan suddenly transformed into Chris Harris there, dropping a legspinner, well short of a length outside off, but Younis saw it and carved it over the infield for a couple
fuller on off and middle, Younis drives it back to the bowler
short again, Younis top-edges a cut he was anyway intending to play aerially, and beats point easily for a couple
back of a length outside off, Misbah stays in the crease and steers behind square
again, short and a touch wide outside off, Misbah fails to place the cut past point
three dots on the trot, fuller from Franklin, Misbah comes forward and looks for the cover drive, but again finds the fielder in the circle

the fielders are on their heels now to save the boundary, so Misbah is allowed a tight single, with a very soft drop into the covers. Younis had to hurry in at the striker's end as Nathan McCullum looked to throw the stumps down
angling in from wide of the crease, Younis works it with the angle to midwicket
a single to round off a quiet over, Younis steers in front of point for a single
back of a length on leg stump, punched wide of mid on for a single
Misbah pulls out a rare piece of improvisation. He pre-meditates the reverse sweep, gets one in the slot around off stump and laps it away along the ground for a couple to third man
turning down the leg side, Misbah gets across and nurdles behind square for one
Younis hangs back to one that turns in from wide outside off and flicks in front of square. Singles are being stolen everywhere.
short of a length outside off, Misbah plays it back to the bowler

huge appeal for lbw, but it is turned down. Misbah set himself up for the sweep, did not make very clean contact. It could have been bat first, it could have hit outside the line of the stumps. Umpire Steve Davis gave it not out and gave it as a run.
133 kph, a hint of curve back into the right hander. Misbah gets the front foot across and drives into the covers. Southee runs all the way up to Misbah in his follow through and says "Hi"

and how does Misbah respond to Southee's pleasantry? He decides to bash the next ball through wide mid on. He possibly decided on the shot before the ball was delivered. It was short of a length, not in the slot at all, but he just went through with a clean swing and made good connection. Nice hit, fine shot to end the boundary drought since the 15th over.
shortens the length, Misbah seemed to expect it, he was hanging back in the crease and chipped it square off the pads for a couple. The force is with Pakistan here.
short ball outside off, Misbah gets back and cuts into the off side for one
tight line on off stump, Younis looks to pinch a single but plays it too softly and it goes nowhere in the off side

ooh, risky but that is four more for Pakistan. Swinging away gently from a foot outside off at 136 kph, Younis moves the front foot across and looks for the drive. He sees he is not close enough and tries to adjust with the wrists, but is still not in complete control. It flew in the air, but to the left of point and through for four more.
Misbah seems to prefer the pace on the ball. He stays in the crease and guides a short ball through cover point for a couple more
full delivery outside off, Misbah flows into an extra cover drive, but can't get the placement
Franklin drops this wide and just back of a length at 126 kph. Misbah reaches across to guide it square.
Misbah shuffles across outside the line of off, and then defends a length ball into the off side
this one angles in from wide of the crease, Misbah gets inside the line and quietly tucks it through wide mid-on for another single
short ball outside off, not enough room for the booming cut that Younis had intended. He ends up steering it into the covers for a tight single
short again outside off, Younis times the cut well, but on the bounce to point
back of a length on off stump, seemed to move away off the deck and Younis was slightly squared up. He managed to open the face and guide it to point again

back of a length again, the kind of ball you can't do much with, except pinch a single. That's exactly what they do. Younis in prime middle-overs milking mode here. Drops it softly towards backward point and hurries across
Misbah waits for a back of length ball to get beside him and then helps it along to third man with an opened face. Another single
again short of a length outside off and Younis guides it into the covers. For a change, no single this time
how close was that to being wided? Bouncer at 126 kph, he chooses to duck under it. That was quite short.
angles into the pads from wide of the crease, another back foot nudge to midwicket. Another single. This must be infuriating for Vettori.
fuller outside off, Younis goes in the air over the covers for a single to the deep

Misbah rolls along. Another full ball outside off, he goes down on a knee and booms it away through the covers with authority. Nathan McCullum does well to run across from sweeper-cover to stop that inside the boundary
full outside off again, another crisp cover drive from Misbah, this time he finds Vettori at extra cover
Misbah walks across the stumps and defends a back of length ball on off stump to the leg side of the pitch

Miabah is turning it on here. Short ball, angled into the body, the line was good, but the lack of pace did not help. Misbah's tendency to hang back on the back foot helped his cause, as he shifted the weight back and thumped the pull shot in between deep midwicket and deep square leg. Pakistan are toying with this chase now.
back of a length, banged in with purpose and hustling Younis onto the back foot. He looks to play to the off side, but misses
short again, registers at 131 kph, Younis jumps back and defends to the off side
angles into the pads, Younis gets inside the line and looks to whip into the leg side, but can't get it away
short ball again, outside off, Younis stays back and steers in front of square for one

Misbah walks right across his stumps and leaves himself prone for an lbw as Bennett spears this in at pace from outside off. Misbah is good enough to turn the blade at the right moment for a single through square leg
full ball on middle and leg, Younis looks for the on drive, but can't place the shot
full on leg stump, he leans out and drives back straight
back of a length on the pads, Younis stays back and works it square for a single
Misbah backs away and looks for the cut, and gets it away past point for one more
Younis leans out, drives with the spin towards mid off
sliding down the leg side this time, Younis looks to glance it fine, but can't get it away for runs
full on off stump, Younis drives into the covers and takes another tight single. For a change, the stumps are hit, but he makes his ground in time

Majestic Misbah marauds merrily to bring up his half-century. Full delivery on off stump, he just shows the bat maker's name as he eases it straight back past the bowler ramrod straight. This is a fine innings.
132 kph, short ball, catches Misbah by surprise as he looks to pull. It pops up off the splice, but lands short of short midwicket. For a change, it does not carry to him.
another short ball, he goes back in the crease and controls the pull better. Single to midwicket
Younis darts inside the line and glances a short ball sliding down the leg side for a single towards fine leg
Misbah is early into the cover drive, and nearly pops it into the fielder's hands. On the bounce to cover.

Younis is gone. New Zealand have a wicket against the run of play, and somewhat against the theme of this partnership. Younis watches closely as Vettori turns one away marginally from middle and leg line. He opens the face and guides it fatally close to point as he takes off for a single. He realises his error a moment too late and turns back, but slips and falls a couple of yards out. Easy collection for Brendon McCullum and the stumps are broken.
back of a length on middle and leg, he goes back and works it against the spin through midwicket for one
fuller on middle and leg, Misbah reaches out and defends to the leg side
on the pads, Misbah presses across and works it off the pads for a single through midwicket
looped up on middle and leg, Umar reaches out and defends down the track
more loop and guile from Vettori, tossed up invitingly at 76 kph, but Umar resists and defends
short ball, tight line just outside off, Misbah rides the bounce and steers square for one
another bouncer from Bennett who is really putting a lot of effort into this spell. 134 kph and whizzes past Umar who weaves away
short ball again, angling into the body and Umar nudges it behind square for a single
back of a length outside off, Misbah reaches out and looks for the square drive. Guptill at point goes acrobatic to deny the single.
full length on middle and off, Misbah drops it quietly into the covers for a single
back of a length to end the over, Umar defends from the crease. We have an interesting finish on our hands here.
served up on the toes, and drifting further down as Misbah leans out, but he is good enough to work it square for one
more defence from Umar, leans out and defends to the off side
Umar advances down the track and gets to the pitch, but can't time the cover drive past the fielder
full toss on the pads, Umar works it through midwicket for one
short ball, straightening from middle and leg, Misbah rocks back and forces it through wide mid on for a single

my goodness, Umar timed that incredibly well. Full delivery from Vettori, but it was a foot wide outside off, giving Umar room for the carved cover-drive. He powered it away off the middle off the bat and deep point had no chance to stop it as it sped past
back of a length outside off, Misbah steers it very late behind square for a single
full on off, Umar decides to play watchfully to the off side
beats the outside edge outside off stump with a touch of away movement from the track. Umar was all over the place, walking across and then feeling for a ball that wasn't full enough for the drive
fuller on off stump, Umar drives into the covers for one
Misbah is looking to manufacture runs here, goes up and over with an on-the-up extra cover drive, and picks up a couple
and this time he walks right across to off stump and flicks a full delivery square for one. He thinks of two and then decides against it
off cutter at 107 kph, comes in from outside off and Misbah swipes through midwicket for one
back of a length, it stops on Umar, who waits and then taps it through mid on for another single
inch-perfect yorker from Styris. Only 110 kph, but Misbah still can't get it away
dropped short, at 107 kph, Misbah gets under it and whacks the leather off it, but he finds deep midwicket.
Umar looks to steer a full ball wide outside off and misses. It is getting tense out there.
on the pads, Umar gets inside the line and nurdles straight to short fine leg for a single that gives him strike

and Umar perishes! His listless innings may be crucial in the end analysis. He backs away to the leg side. Vettori sees him going and fires it full aiming at the pads. Umar manages to still get beside the line and tries to carve it inside out. He is too close to the ball to get it over the circle and plays it straight into a tumbling extra cover's hands.

and Boom Boom bashes his first ball. Backs away again, Vettori sees him again, but doesn't go too full this time. It is back of a length and there's enough room for Afridi to get under it and muscle it over the covers.

Boom Boom goes bust. Vettori has nailed him and this game might be turning around here. Afridi goes the other way this time, walks across to off stump and looks for the sweep. Vettori sticks to his guns and lands it full and in line with middle and leg. Afridi failed to connect and it hit him in front of middle and leg. He's not very pleased with the decision though. It hit the back leg, that seemed adjacent
full and fired just outside off, Razzaq can't connect with the steer

Razzaq survives a run-out chance. Tries to force this off the back foot from outside off into the covers, and then takes off for a tough single. Nathan McCullum missed the stumps at the bowlers' end with Razzaq well out, and conceded an overthrow
superb over from Dan. Full on the toes, nothing Razzaq can do with it, except dig it out to the leg side for a single

Absolute brutality. Violence. Razzaq has smashed this. Short ball from Southee, Razzaq camps well back in the crease and just swats it away over midwicket with the arrogance ordinary people would reserve for swatting flies.
fuller, he looks to launch this over long on and nearly holes out. On the bounce to the deep
well bowler, very full on middle and leg, Misbah can't do much except take a meek single to gthe leg side
Southee has wisely resorted to the yorkers. Razzaq looks to smear it over the leg side if it's there for the shot, but it isn't.

Misbah has stoles four here, with some help from the forces above. He chips away to off stump and works it through the huge gap on the leg side. Williamson runs back like his life depends on it and dives headlong towards the boundary, and pulls it back in, but it hits Nathan McCullum's  boots as he covers up behind Williamson and trickles back over the boundary

Misbah you beauty! Amid the frenzy of the situation, he's picking off boundaries with the most delicate array of shots. Full delivery on off, he quietly moves away to off stump and turns his wrists. Timed even better than last time. Williamson had no chance. Superb batting.
third man is up and Razzaq looks to steer one past the man inside the circle, but he is completely cramped for room and can't get it it away fine. Gets a single to the right of short third man
back of a length outside off, Misbah looks the dab, and gets a single to short third man

Bennett's bowling neither yorkers, nor length deliveries. He's keeping it much shorter while cramping Razzaq for room. Smart option as long as it works. Razzaq forces this one without timing into the covers for one

well, he will smoke it through the packed cover cordon, that's what he will do! Another special shot from the Misbah armoury, it is full, and as always Bennett doesn't give him much room to work with, but inb his current form, Misbah doesn't need much room. He just stays beside the line and slams it along the ground through the covers.
he walks across to the off stump now. Geez. he's walked around his crease almost as much as he has run between the wickets today! Turns the wrists and gets another single square
Razzaq nearly chops this one back onto the stumps as he looks to steer square. Misbah runs like a man possessed and they take a single
yorker at 128 kph, Razzaq is waiting for any indiscretion in length, but Southee offers none on this occasion. Razzaq digs it back down the track and Southee fields

goes for another yorker, misses the mark by a couple of inches. That's enough for Razzaq to get his biceps under, and nearly blast through Vettori at mid off. Vettori does well to slow it down and limit the damage to two.
and the yorker again, this time Razzaq plays it straight to Vettori and pulls out of the single late.
Southee gets away with a full toss at 128 kph on the pads. Razzaq gets inside the line and whips it with a violent flourish, but finds the man at deep midwicket
Misbah hangs back in the crease and looks to heave Southee with the angle through midwicket, but can't make very good connection. There is cover in the deep, so just a single
another near-yorker - at 132 kph on leg stump, Razzaq scoops it past the bowler to the on side, without much timing, for a single. Well bowled, Tim Southee.

a decisive blow. Full on off stump, Razzaq moves away and lines it up for the extra cover drive. Vettori at mid off wasn't too far away, but he hardly made an effort. He is clearly struggling with a hamstring niggle. Four to Pakistan.
Razzaq backs away and slashes a short ball outside off through backward point. Another single.

Misbah digs deep into the recesses of the crease to convert the yorker lengths into half-volleys. It was full on off stump and he managed to time the heave through midwicket, but New Zealand now have cover there

stupendous stuff from Baz behind the stumps. Razzaq backs away and looks to smear a short ball over midwicket, it slips through, under the bat and wide of leg stump before an acrobatic dive from Brendon to his left

The game seesaws once again. Pakistan lose another wicket in the Powerplay. Bennett keeps it full, but not full enough to stop Razzaq. He gets under it and looks to launch it over the off side, but it hits very low on the bat and as a result, is scooped up high into the Napier night. When it came down, Vettori was under it.
angled into the pads, Misbah times the flick well but finds deep midwicket again. It is a single, which means he will retain strike.
and the length is awry, first ball. 110 kph off cutter, well short of a length on off stump, Misbah must have been beside himself with glee as he lined that up and blasted it over midwicket. Bang!
Misbah is taking it away! Fuller from Styris, but too full this time. Misbah twinkles away to middle and off and then drills this over wide mid on. Couple of bounces, four. What impeccable placement!

and the single now, that's all they need from here. Misbah drops a length ball on off stump into the covers and turns the strike over. Can Riaz hold his nerve? He can bat alright. As can Gul, who is in next.
yorker, tight on off stump, Riaz can't do much with it. He digs it out straight to cover

Oh Riaz! What has he done here? Short of length at friendly pace outside off, he goes down on a knee and looks for an ugly hoick across the line. The shot was so not on. He was so not in the position to pull it off. Top edge, balloons up to the right of Brendon McCullum who trots back and pouches it easily.

and Misbah can't get the single to retain strike! Slow off cutter in line with off stump, Misbah backs away and looks to guide it through the cordon on the off side, but can't hit the gap. Sohail backs up a mile before hurrying back into the crease

and Sohail has smacked it back past the bowler with disdain! Length ball from Southee on leg stump, Sohail just drills it through mid on for four. Nobody moved. Vettori didn't have a chance, injury or not.

boy, he can hit 'em! He can hit them with a straight bat. He can hit them with a horizontal bat. And he can hit them into the safest gap in the field - straight behind the bowler. This was short of a length and angling across Sohain who played an authoritative forehand slap back down the ground.

better length, but Sohail is alert to the situation. It is fuller outside off, Sohail opens the face and runs it fine for a couple to third man. Bennett barely manages to haul it in, and save two runs.
short ball, well wide outside off stump and Sohail looks to swat it square. And misses! Drama everywhere.
short again, but no room this time for Sohail to play the steer. He still tries, mind you. Too close for comfort and he misses. Through to Baz. Another dot. Can Southee end the over on a high?

He can't! Sohail has finished it off with another booming boundary. Why is he batting at No. 10? This is some tail that Pakistan have, it is hardly a tail. Short ball from Southee, angling across at decent pace. Sohail has figured out the short line of attack and pulls it majestically over the packed infield. Misbah and Sohail join hands mid-pitch and smile in relief. Majestic Misbah marches off with a masterly 93, his career-best score. What a finish. Pakistan 2 New Zealand 1. With two to play.
